{"id": "EUVD-2022-54767", "enisaUuid": "c89264c4-81d1-37af-bbc5-ac04331246de", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ndrm/msm/a6xx: Fix refcount leak in a6xx_gpu_init\n\nof_parse_phandle() returns a node pointer with refcount\nincremented, we should use of_node_put() on it when not need anymore.\n\na6xx_gmu_init() passes the node to of_find_device_by_node()\nand of_dma_configure(), of_find_device_by_node() will takes its\nreference, of_dma_configure() doesn't need the node after usage.\n\nAdd missing of_node_put() to avoid refcount leak.", "datePublished": "2025-02-26T02:13:09", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-01T19:46:47", "baseScore": 5.5, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/6832e36f156ea35a6ed74bca72727806116effdd", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/48e82ce8cdb19c20a5020fa446b286d6a147450c", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/edff4c1af831d0c02e654eed9da7d74174de49d5", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/65ddbc0d26824e2a5d6154d01d8cf39344900213", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/06907a374f1b74f8f2fb30720dc6df81331e4fb5", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/c56de483093d7ad0782327f95dda7da97bc4c315", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-49462"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-49462"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.04, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "06cc8833-7847-38a9-92fa-3be6f467078f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "1e1bcb28-087e-3d1e-8de8-64b324ae1945", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "4b565ca5a2cbbbb6345e8789da89c193b6b00e5a <edff4c1af831d0c02e654eed9da7d74174de49d5"}, {"id": "48c948cb-a327-37a2-a2e6-224fbc315362", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "4b565ca5a2cbbbb6345e8789da89c193b6b00e5a <48e82ce8cdb19c20a5020fa446b286d6a147450c"}, {"id": "5606d351-bbf7-3f66-8fa3-686f911d20dc", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.19"}, {"id": "59989945-f1dc